			<title>Graphics Tips</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=58377&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Fri, 30 May 2008 16:24:17 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[Ok here are a few things to help fix your graphic FPS!

First things first, if you are really having problems...

Remove your driver in safe mode, run driver sweeper, reboot into safe mode, remove your standard VGA adapter, reboot again and install new driver.

Next, for whatever reason the "High"...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Ok here are a few things to help fix your graphic FPS!<br />
<br />
First things first, if you are really having problems...<br />
<br />
Remove your driver in safe mode, run driver sweeper, reboot into safe mode, remove your standard VGA adapter, reboot again and install new driver.<br />
<br />
Next, for whatever reason the &quot;High&quot; graphics setting works better then &quot;Low&quot; just turn off shadows entirely after using it.<br />
<br />
And lastly an old CS trick, running WMP idle in the background will help loading times and give a few FPS.</div>

]]></content:encoded>
