			<title>Update notes, 26th of may 2008</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=58294&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Mon, 26 May 2008 10:31:48 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>From here (http://forums-eu.ageofconan.com/showthread.php?t=15040).

*Update Notes - 26th of May*
Barbarian in Reaver Stance now correctly moves at slower speed while hiding

Fixed an exploit with Demonologists (infinite stacking of certain spells)

Hostile spells casted by the player on itself...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>From <a href="http://forums-eu.ageofconan.com/showthread.php?t=15040" target="_blank">here</a>.<br />
<br />
<b>Update Notes - 26th of May</b><br />
Barbarian in Reaver Stance now correctly moves at slower speed while hiding<br />
<br />
Fixed an exploit with Demonologists (infinite stacking of certain spells)<br />
<br />
Hostile spells casted by the player on itself should no longer trigger reactive spell procs.<br />
<br />
The main reason for this update was to fix an exploit concerning demonologists.<br />
<br />
Updating is sometimes a tricky thing as we have to make sure not to introduce new issues when solving another one. We know there are still other things to fix and the plan is to patch again very soon.<br />
<br />
Thank you.<br />
-------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
They need to fix traders and banks ASAP. As much as I liked the launch, there is really no excuse for launching a game with no working auction house or banks.<br />
<br />
Hopefully they'll patch soon, I need to get my hands on decent green/blue 2-hand blunt weapon.</div>

]]></content:encoded>
